From: Darren Starr <darren@example.com>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 23:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] fs/nfs/nfs4client.c: create extra dnfs transports

Create additional RPC transports to each address in the remoteaddrs=
list immediately after the NFSv4.1 session is established.

This function is called from nfs4_create_session() after the session
is confirmed. For each address in the dnfs address list (excluding
the primary address which already has a transport), a new TCP
connection is created via rpc_clnt_add_xprt() and added to the
client's xprt_switch.

The stock xprt_switch round-robin dispatch automatically distributes
subsequent NFS operations across all transports — no dispatch code
changes are needed.

TRANSPORT CREATION STRATEGY

- Each address gets one TCP connection (future: support nconnect per addr)
- Connections are created sequentially (future: parallel creation)
- Failed connections are logged but do not fail the mount
- The primary transport is always available

SESSION COMPATIBILITY

We do NOT call BIND_CONN_TO_SESSION. Standard NFSv4.1 servers accept
operations on any connection carrying a valid session ID. If a server
requires explicit connection binding (strict RFC compliance), the
client falls back gracefully — only the primary transport is used.

Signed-off-by: Darren Starr <darren@example.com>
---
 fs/nfs/nfs4client.c | 89 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 89 insertions(+)

diff --git a/fs/nfs/nfs4client.c b/fs/nfs/nfs4client.c
index 1033e3a..b09e5ca 100644
--- a/fs/nfs/nfs4client.c
+++ b/fs/nfs/nfs4client.c
@@ -64,6 +64,82 @@ static int nfs4_setup_session_callback(struct nfs_client *clp)
 	return 0;
 }

+#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_DNFS)
+/**
+ * nfs4_dnfs_create_xprts - Create extra transports for dnfs
+ * @clp: NFS client with an established NFSv4.1 session
+ *
+ * Called after nfs4_create_session() succeeds. Creates additional
+ * RPC transports to each address in the client's dnfs remote address
+ * list and adds them to the transport switch for round-robin dispatch.
+ *
+ * The primary transport to the mount target server is already created
+ * by rpc_create(). This function only creates transports for the
+ * ADDITIONAL addresses from the remoteaddrs= mount option.
+ *
+ * Return: 0 on success (partial success is still success),
+ *         negative errno on failure.
+ */
+int nfs4_dnfs_create_xprts(struct nfs_client *clp)
+{
+	struct dnfs_address_list *list;
+	struct rpc_clnt *clnt;
+	int i, ret;
+	int success = 0, failed = 0;
+
+	/*
+	 * Validate prerequisites: must have a client with an RPC client
+	 * and a populated dnfs address list.
+	 */
+	if (!clp || !clp->cl_rpcclient)
+		return -EINVAL;
+
+	list = clp->cl_dnfs_info;
+	if (!list || list->count == 0)
+		return 0;
+
+	clnt = clp->cl_rpcclient;
+
+	/*
+	 * Iterate through the address list starting at index 1.
+	 * Index 0 is the primary server — its transport already exists.
+	 * We only create transports for extra addresses.
+	 *
+	 * FUTURE: When the primary server address is not in the list
+	 * (user specifies a different set), we create all transports
+	 * including the primary.
+	 */
+	for (i = 1; i < list->count; i++) {
+		struct sockaddr *sa = (struct sockaddr *)&list->addrs[i];
+		size_t salen = sizeof(list->addrs[i]);
+
+		/*
+		 * Create a new transport to this address and add it
+		 * to the client's xprt_switch.
+		 *
+		 * rpc_clnt_add_xprt() handles TCP connection setup,
+		 * xprt_switch insertion, and connection tracking.
+		 */
+		ret = rpc_clnt_add_xprt(clnt, sa, salen, NULL, NULL);
+		if (ret < 0) {
+			pr_warn("NFS: dnfs: failed to create xprt [%d]: %d\n",
+				i, ret);
+			failed++;
+			continue;
+		}
+
+		success++;
+	}
+
+	if (failed > 0)
+		pr_info("NFS: dnfs: created %d/%d extra transports\n",
+			success, success + failed);
+	else if (success > 0)
+		pr_debug("NFS: dnfs: created %d extra transports\n", success);
+
+	return 0;
+}
+#endif /* CONFIG_DNFS */
+
 /**
  * nfs4_init_client_minor_version - Ensure client is created with
  *				    the correct minor version
@@ -2089,6 +2165,19 @@ int nfs4_create_session(struct nfs_client *clp)
 	else if (status < 0)
 		goto out;

+	/*
+	 * Session is established. If dnfs multipath is configured,
+	 * create additional transports to the addresses specified
+	 * in the remoteaddrs= mount option.
+	 *
+	 * This is intentionally placed after session creation so that
+	 * the new transports can carry operations using the session ID.
+	 */
+	if (IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_DNFS)) {
+		status = nfs4_dnfs_create_xprts(clp);
+		/* Non-fatal: mount proceeds with whatever transports exist. */
+	}
+
 out:
 	return status;
 }
